The stamps were issued on the 25th february, 1925. printed at the offices of the Cape Times, Cape Town, by photo-litho offset process, in sheets of 120 in uper and lower panes, each apne containing six rows of 10 stamps. No watermark, Perf. 12. No marginalc controls; but at top and bottom and twice at the right side of teh sheet appeared a figure of value in a circle, printed in teh colour of the stamps. the stamps were available in post offices till end of June and from P.M.G., Pretoria till 31st October, 1925.



